From: cono <q@cono.org.ua>
Subject: [PATCH] mermaid: use universally-available Linux fonts

usvg's fontdb does literal font-name matching and does not honor
fontconfig aliases, so the upstream default of "Helvetica, Arial,
sans-serif" produces a "no match for font-family" warning and an
ugly fallback on systems without media-fonts/corefonts. Use the
fonts shipped by most desktop installs (media-fonts/dejavu and
media-fonts/liberation-fonts) instead. The "sans-serif" generic
is kept as a final fallback so the assertion in the existing test
that "the SVG should not require Inter" still holds.

--- a/src/mermaid.rs
+++ b/src/mermaid.rs
@@ -18,7 +18,7 @@
 /// Returns an error if the mermaid source cannot be parsed.
 pub fn render_to_svg(mermaid_source: &str) -> Result<String> {
     let mut opts = mermaid_rs_renderer::RenderOptions::default();
-    opts.theme.font_family = "Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif".to_string();
+    opts.theme.font_family = "DejaVu Sans, Liberation Sans, sans-serif".to_string();
     let svg = catch_unwind(AssertUnwindSafe(|| {
         mermaid_rs_renderer::render_with_options(mermaid_source, opts)
     }))
